\int_{0}^{\pi /2}\sin^n x\cdot dx.
\int_0^{\pi /2}\sin^{2n+1}x\cdot dx = \int_0^{\pi /2}\sin x\cdot \sin^{2n}x\cdot dx=\int_0^{\pi /2}\sin x\cdot  (1-cos^2x) ^n\cdot dx
t=\cos(x)
dt=-\sin(x) \, dx
\int_0^{\pi /2}\sin x\cdot  (1-\cos^2x) ^n\cdot dx=-\int_1^0 (1-t^2)^n \, dt
